Definition: from the Sanskrit word for `reflection' or `interpretation') one of six orthodox philosophical systems or viewpoints on ritual traditions rooted in the Vedas and the Brahmanas as opposed to Vedanta which relies mostly on the Upanishads
Synonyms: Hinduism, noun, communication, Sanskrit, c, from, the, word, for, reflection, or, interpretation, one, of, six, orthodox, philosophical, systems, viewpoints, on, ritual, traditions, rooted, in, Vedas, and, Brahmanas, as, opposed, to, Vedanta, which, relies, mostly, Upanishads
Category: noun.cognition
